@mandy12 -- I totally undertand the need for smaller file sizes. You are not alone, there are people with a monthly bandwidth limit or who play on portable devices. However, EZTV only torrents SD (standard definition, typically 720x404) and 720 (typically 1280x720).  Smaller sizes are occaisionally available by other torrent groups, or individuals. 

@Kleavage -- IMMERSE and EVOLVE are names of "Scene" groups who cap (record) the shows. EZTV, TvTeam, ettv, etc, are names of Torrent groups. A torrent title consists of:
Show name, season/episode, dimension (SD is default), source (almost always HDTV), the name of The Scene group that capped the episode, and sometimes a torrent group name is added at the end. 

@William412 -- Simma down warrior man. lol. Some people need the smaller file sizes. 
But for show with a lot of actions scenes and or special effects, like you, I prefer 720

